The paper deals with developing new abstractions and reasoning techniques for differential privacy, which is a topic in both cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a novel construction for reasoning about statistical divergences, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of program logic for proving differential privacy properties suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
